	function [Ratio, Remaind] = LONG_DIV(Pnum, Qden) 	%	Divides the polynomial Pnum with Qden and returns the polynomial, Ratio,	%	and the numerator of the remainder, Remaind.	% 	The polynomials have the highest power first.		% 	Toolbox for DIGITAL FILTERS USING MATLAB		% 	Author: 		Lars Wanhammar 2007-07-22	%	Modified by: 	LW 2016-04-22		% 	Copyright:		by authors - not released for commercial use	% 	Version:		1		% 	Known bugs:			% 	Report bugs to:	Wanhammar@gmail.com		NP = length(Pnum);	NQ = length(Qden);	k = NP-NQ+1;	Ratio = zeros(1, k);	R = Pnum;	for j = 1:k		Ratio(j) = Pnum(j)/Qden(1);		y = zeros(1,k+1-j); y(1) = 1;		R = POLYSUB(R, Ratio(j)*POLYMULT(Qden, y));	end	Remaind(1) = 1;	for j = 1:NP-k		Remaind(j) = R(j+k);	end